🦖 DinoStudios Future Projects List
Planned & Curated by Greyson — Founder of DinoStudios

DinoStudios will continue expanding its archive and research efforts by exploring new dinosaur‑themed media, forgotten Minecraft creations, and childhood worlds that deserve preservation.
Below is the official roadmap of future projects.

⭐ 1. Tankee Dinosaur Media Expansion
Tankee hosted multiple small dinosaur‑related clips and micro‑series that were never documented.
DinoStudios will:

search for additional dinosaur content on Tankee

verify episode lists

archive thumbnails

document any related mod usage

preserve metadata before it disappears

This expands the Dinos Reborn archive into a full Tankee dinosaur collection.

⭐ 2. Minecraft Dinosaur Mod History Project
A long‑term research project covering:

JurassiCraft development history

Fossils & Archeology Revival history

lesser‑known dinosaur mods

abandoned dinosaur mod projects

early versions and lost builds

mod creators and community contributions

This will become a full historical timeline of Minecraft dinosaur modding.

⭐ 3. “Forgotten Dinosaur Shows” Database
A curated list of dinosaur‑themed media that:

aired on small platforms

had limited distribution

were removed from streaming

had no community discussion

were never archived properly

Each entry will include:

description

platform

release year

status (found / partially found / lost)

recovery notes

DinoStudios will aim to recover as many as possible.

⭐ 4. Minecraft World Reconstruction Projects
Using screenshots, memories, and mod analysis, DinoStudios will attempt to reconstruct:

the Dinos Reborn lab

the barn

the jeep area

the biome exploration paths

the dinosaur nursery

any unique structures from the show

These reconstructions will be documented as research builds.

⭐ 5. “Childhood Dinosaur Memories” Archive
A community‑driven archive where people can submit:

dinosaur shows they remember

games they played

mods they used

books they read

toys they loved

DinoStudios will investigate submissions and attempt to locate or preserve them.

⭐ 6. Lost Dinosaur Games Investigation
Many dinosaur games from the 2000s–2010s are partially lost or undocumented.
Future investigations include:

mobile dinosaur games removed from app stores

Flash dinosaur games

early Roblox dinosaur worlds

obscure PC dinosaur titles

dinosaur educational software

Each case will be researched and archived.

⭐ 7. DinoStudios Documentation Standards
Creation of official standards for:

case reports

mod analysis

world reconstruction

platform navigation guides

archival formatting

This ensures future projects maintain the same quality as the Dinos Reborn case.

⭐ 8. DinoStudios Preservation Vault
A long‑term digital vault containing:

screenshots

notes

mod lists

platform instructions

research logs

case files

world reconstructions

This vault will serve as the permanent home for all DinoStudios findings.

🏁 The Future of DinoStudios
DinoStudios will continue to grow as a one‑person mission dedicated to preserving dinosaur media that would otherwise be forgotten.
Every project strengthens the archive.
Every recovery protects a memory.
Every case keeps a world alive.

This is the roadmap.
This is the mission.
This is DinoStudios.
